JOHANNESBURG - The horror film 'The Tokoloshe' is set to send shivers across the globe. The film is directed by Jerome Pikwane with a script he co-wrote with novelist Richard Kunzmann, over a period of 10 years. READ: 'Inxeba' no longer classified as hardcore porn The psychological horror has been selected for prestigious global film festivals, including The Bucheon International Fantastic Film Festival in South Korea and South Africa’s very own Durban International Film Festival. *View the attached video where the film’s producers Dumi Gumbi and Cati Weinek give an insight into what viewers can expect. eNCA